      "content": "This is a common and often frustrating issue with student loans, and it's almost always due to how interest is calculated. If your loan has a high interest rate, a significant portion of your monthly payment is going straight to covering the accrued interest, leaving very little to chip away at the principal balance. To see the principal decrease faster, you might consider making extra payments or exploring refinancing options.",
